 I had ordered Dr Morepen Omega 3. 
 500 mg Fish oil  
   
 But your company delivered me the medicine with Triple Strength of 1250 mg Fish Oil. 
   
 This is utter ridiculous and serious. 
   
 You should deliver only the medicine I had ordered Yesterday. If it is not in your stock do not deliver it. 
   
 But without my consent you had delivered 1250 mg Fish oil. 
   
 It is not allowing me to return on your application. 
   
 Request you to immediately return it and send me the full refund for this medicine I had paid (amount paid yesterday+ Rs 428.54 additional today). 
 
 Hoping immediately quick return and refund

 Shobhit

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Partnerships Team,

Greetings.

I am Sireesha, writing to inquire about PharmEasy partnership opportunities
in Hyderabad, specifically for store-based or dark-store models that
support online and quick medicine delivery.

I am interested in understanding PharmEasy’s partner-led operational model
and would appreciate details on:

Available partnership models (store partner / dark store/hub)

1. Investment requirement and setup cost

2. Revenue sharing or margin structure

3. Expected monthly order volume and profit potential

4. Delivery radius and operational responsibilities

5. Inventory ownership and expiry risk management

6. Technology and logistics support provided

7. Eligibility for 10–30 minute delivery models

8. Ideal localities and minimum area requirements

9. Onboarding timeline and expansion opportunities

I am exploring high-demand areas such as Madhapur, Hitech City, Kondapur,
and Kukatpally.

Kindly let me know the next steps to proceed.

-- 
Thanks & Regards
Sireesha Athota

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Partnerships Team,

Greetings.

I am Sireesha, writing to inquire about PharmEasy partnership opportunities
in Hyderabad, specifically for store-based or dark-store models that
support online and quick medicine delivery.

I am interested in understanding PharmEasy’s partner-led operational model
and would appreciate details on:

Available partnership models (store partner / dark store/hub)

1. Investment requirement and setup cost

2. Revenue sharing or margin structure

3. Expected monthly order volume and profit potential

4. Delivery radius and operational responsibilities

5. Inventory ownership and expiry risk management

6. Technology and logistics support provided

7. Eligibility for 10–30 minute delivery models

8. Ideal localities and minimum area requirements

9. Onboarding timeline and expansion opportunities

I am exploring high-demand areas such as Madhapur, Hitech City, Kondapur,
and Kukatpally.

Kindly let me know the next steps to proceed.

-- 
Thanks & Regards
Sireesha Athota
+1 518 870 8041

--

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Hi Team,

This is the most disgusting experience ever that i have had with any Medicine Provider, I shop with local pharmacies, brands like you, Tata 1 MG, Apollo and even hospitals as well.

This is the sugar monitor sensor, we are taking about in the order and what i received was an open box with a used sensor delivered to me, with hair visble on the sensor meaning someone had used it ??? and don't question me on my integrity which may be a escape route you might take saying i may have used it and i am asking for a refund now,, i am not that person as I am very calm while writing this email, which I should not be.  d

Are you serious? how can someone from your warehouse be so unprofessional such that they didnt even check a returned packet and also sent the same to another customer??? do you understand what that means about your warehousing standards etc.
Crazy to say the least, i am a Plus member since long and i have preferred pharmeasy for years but how can you do this?

I expect an apology and a complete refund of my money.

Thanks
Amit Sharma

--

Subject: Refund Still Not Credited to PharmEasy Wallet Despite Confirmation

Dear PharmEasy Team,

This is to inform you that despite your confirmation stating that the
Express Delivery fee of ₹5 would be refunded to my PharmEasy wallet, the
amount has still not been credited till date.

I have been continuously following up through emails, but there is no
update or visible refund in my wallet. This ongoing delay and lack of
proper information is causing unnecessary inconvenience.

Details:

Issue: Refund not reflecting in PharmEasy wallet

Confirmed Refund Amount: ₹5 (Express Delivery fee)

Current Status: Not credited yet


I request you to kindly credit the refund immediately and share a clear
confirmation with transaction reference.

If the refund is not processed within 24 hours, I will be forced to

Helpline for deficiency in service.

Kindly treat this as urgent.

Sincerely,
Name: Praveen Sharma

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear Pharmeasy team,

I hope you’re having a great day! My name is Nishtha Hemnani and I’m
reaching out on behalf of the *Social Outreach and Enabling Center (SOEC)*
at *Fergusson Autonomous College, Pune*—one of the most prestigious
institutions in the city.

We are gearing up for our *Departmental Fest* on *29th & 30th December* on
campus, and we’d love to have you on board as a sponsor. The fest attracts
*50,000–60,000 participants*, offering massive brand visibility.

*Sponsorship perks we offer:*
- Standee presence at the venue
- Logo on event T‑shirts (size/placement tailored to your sponsorship
amount)
- Professionally shot dedicated reel and Instagram Stories
- Google Reviews: We’ll encourage attendees to leave reviews and tag your
brand.
- Shout‑out during the event: Your brand will be mentioned live in our
closing remarks.
- Distribution of your promotional materials to all attendees

We have a range of sponsorship packages to suit different budgets and

notes.body: Hello Kingshuk,     Greetings from PharmEasy!  I am sorry to inform you that your orders #658417178834272256-29764 and 659397775835025408-99954 were cancelled due to the medicine that you added being unavailable with our Partner Retailer. I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you. ​  Please note, at the time of placing the order the requested medicine was available in limited quantity, and you were able to add medicines in the order. Once the medicine was added to your order, our Partner Retailer tried to arrange the medicine from every possible source. However, they could not arrange one. I apologize that we were unable to fulfill your medicine requirements for this order completely.  I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. As our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request you to reach us out. We will highlight your concern to the Partner retailer.     For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the 'Need Help' section.  Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay Healthy.    Regards,     Devdas.
notes.body_html:
Hello Kingshuk,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

I am sorry to inform you that your orders #658417178834272256-29764 and 659397775835025408-99954 were cancelled due to the medicine that you added being unavailable with our Partner Retailer. I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you. ​

Please note, at the time of placing the order the requested medicine was available in limited quantity, and you were able to add medicines in the order. Once the medicine was added to your order, our Partner Retailer tried to arrange the medicine from every possible source. However, they could not arrange one. I apologize that we were unable to fulfill your medicine requirements for this order completely.

I request you to place a new order after 7 days for the required medicine. As our retailer restocks the medicines every 7 days. If the medicine is still unavailable, I would request you to reach us out. We will highlight your concern to the Partner retailer.

For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the 'Need Help' section.

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay Healthy.

Regards,
Devdas.
